<p>Stephen Menn, currently Professor of Philosophy at <a href="https://www.mcgill.ca/philosophy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">McGill University</a>, will be moving to the <a href="https://philosophy.utoronto.ca/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">University of Toronto</a>, where he will be the inaugural holder of the Michael and Virginia Walsh Chair in the History of Philosophy.<span id="more-55493"></span></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-55502 aligncenter" src="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/menn-stephen.jpg" alt="" width="210" height="240" /></p>
<p>The position was endowed by a <a href="https://dailynous.com/2024/01/08/toronto-philosophy-receives-5-million-endowment-for-new-chair/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">significant gift</a> by the Walsh&#8217;s to the Toronto Department of Philosophy last year.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.mcgill.ca/philosophy/stephen-menn" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Professor Menn</a> specializes in ancient philosophy, Medieval philosophy (including Islamic philosophy), and the history and philosophy of mathematics. He is the author of <em>Plato on God as Nous </em>(1995), <em>Descartes and AugustineÂ </em>(1998), and many other works, which you can learn more about <a href="https://philpapers.org/asearch.pl?strict=1&amp;searchStr=Menn,%20Stephen&amp;filterMode=authors" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>.</p>
<p>Menn will continue to hold an honorary professorship at Humboldt University of Berlin. In addition to his appointment in Philosophy at Toronto, he will also be a member of the graduate faculty in Classics.</p>
<p>He takes up his new position at Toronto in January, 2026.</p>
